1
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:08,320
Aunt Nong?

2
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,400
Uncle Rut.

3
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:16,320
Aunt Nong…

4
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:44,920
Aunt Nong!

5
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:47,040
Aunt Nong.

6
00:03:48,480 --> 00:03:49,520
Aunt Nong!

7
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Uh…

8
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:37,680
So what were those two arguing about?

9
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:45,240
Well, it's just that…

10
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:48,360
Mr. Warat…

11
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:53,480
He's actually not Mr. Wichan's son.

12
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,520
Oh?

13
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:58,560
And what does that have to do

14
00:04:58,640 --> 00:05:00,880
with Kluay and Mr. Warat?

15
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:02,880
What's their problem?

16
00:05:04,280 --> 00:05:06,680
Mr. Warat thinks

17
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:10,640
he's been deceiving Ms. Kluay.

18
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:13,840
- Oh come on, deceiving her how?
- Mm.

19
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:17,200
Well, before this he had wealth, status,

20
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:21,000
and came from a well-known family.

21
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:22,960
But now he has nothing left.

22
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:31,200
Did I say something wrong?

23
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:35,000
Kluay doesn't even know
who her parents are.

24
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:36,680
Why would she care

25
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:39,920
whether Mr. Warat
is part of the Vanich family or not?

26
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,920
- Well…
- That doesn't matter at all.

27
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,400
I know my daughter well.

28
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:49,040
The one we should
be worried about is Mr. Warat.

29
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:54,360
Yes, he looks really disappointed.

30
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:58,960
Of course he is,

31
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:01,480
but he just wants to take responsibility.

32
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:04,000
Responsibility for what?

33
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:07,840
To find Ms. Waree.

34
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:11,160
And once he finds her,
he'll return all the assets to her

35
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:13,400
so he can walk his own path.

36
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:17,680
But even if that's true,
that's no reason to break up with Kluay.

37
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:21,760
From what I've seen of him,

38
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:25,840
that doesn't seem like the reason
he'd break up with Ms. Kluay.

39
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:29,840
I hope so.

40
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:40,400
What happened, Mom?

41
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:42,880
Why did I suddenly

42
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,920
become Mr. Sarut's son?

43
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,920
Does everything

44
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:53,200
have to end with me?

45
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:56,520
Does it, Mom?

46
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:11,640
Mr. Warat.

47
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:15,320
Earlier,
I was sitting in front of the mirror

48
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,680
and I saw…

49
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,720
Is this because of me?

50
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:06,000
I dragged you into all this.

51
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:09,400
No. I chose this myself.

52
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,720
- Mr. Warat.
- Ms. Ampha.

53
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:14,760
Can you hear me?

54
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,360
From now on,

55
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:22,120
don't communicate with Kluay anymore.

56
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:26,320
If you need anything,

57
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:29,360
talk to me instead.

58
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:34,240
I can feel it too.
Do you hear me, Ms. Ampha?

59
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:38,320
What are you trying to do?

60
00:08:40,039 --> 00:08:41,240
I'm glad you asked.

61
00:08:43,880 --> 00:08:46,320
I was just about to tell you something.

62
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,640
What is it?

63
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:54,560
All this time, Kluay…

64
00:08:58,280 --> 00:09:00,200
I've been using you.

65
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:04,400
Because I thought
it would make things easier.

66
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:09,480
Okay.

67
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:13,040
From now on, stay away from me.

68
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:18,200
Mr. Warat, don't do this.

69
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:23,920
I'm being honest with you, I used you.

70
00:09:24,680 --> 00:09:26,200
You're no longer useful to me.

71
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:28,760
Kluay,

72
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,240
let's break up.

73
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:37,040
Um…

74
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,080
What…

75
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,720
What really happened?

76
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:46,640
Like I said,

77
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:49,440
I never had feelings for you.

78
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,520
We're done, okay?

79
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:57,200
There's just one thing I ask.
No matter what happens,

80
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:59,080
don't leave this house.

81
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:03,640
As for us,

82
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:08,240
it's over.

83
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:10,040
Don't get involved with me again.

84
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:14,800
And about Ms. Ampha… Ms. Ampha,

85
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:19,120
don't contact Kluay anymore.
If anything, talk to me.

86
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:22,600
- Kluay…
- Mr. Warat.

87
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:23,560
Well…

88
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:30,560
What?

89
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:45,960
Aunt Nong.

90
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:49,440
Aunt Nong.

91
00:10:57,760 --> 00:10:58,880
Aunt Nong.

92
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,560
Aunt Nong.

93
00:11:18,160 --> 00:11:19,240
Aunt Nong.

94
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:22,920
Aunt Nong.

95
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:29,240
Now you only have me left as your family.

96
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:33,320
What are you doing in here?
What's in this room?

97
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:36,920
Aunt Nong, you can tell me anything.

98
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:40,000
Is there something
you want to talk to me about?

99
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:44,680
Aunt Nong.

100
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,920
Listen to me.

101
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:52,920
Whenever you're ready,
you can tell me anytime.

102
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:55,560
There are only the two of us

103
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:58,480
left in this world.

104
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:01,840
I won't…

105
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:05,840
I won't trust anyone else

106
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,320
except you.

107
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:28,360
<i>Happy 12-hour anniversary</i>

108
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:31,200
<i>of being together.</i>

109
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,200
Surprise!

110
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:07,520
Are you okay?

111
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:12,760
<i>I broke up with Mr. Warat, Som.</i>

112
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,400
What?

113
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:15,520
They really broke up.

114
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:19,560
What's wrong?

115
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:27,320
Mr. Warat and Kluay broke up.

116
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,360
Huh?

117
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:52,400
- What is this?
- I need you to find this person.

118
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:54,520
How old is this photo?

119
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,880
About 20-something years.

120
00:13:57,480 --> 00:14:00,560
If it's adults,
I might still be able to find them.

121
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:02,480
Those two adults are already dead.

122
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:04,680
Then you want me to find--

123
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:06,440
The little girl in this photo.

124
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:08,040
You…

125
00:14:08,120 --> 00:14:11,520
I know it's difficult, but if you succeed…

126
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:16,240
Alright.

127
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,600
Let me review all the information first.

128
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,720
All the documents are prepared.

129
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:32,560
I don't think this will work.
We weren't framed with fake documents.

130
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:34,560
Why do you think that?

131
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:37,600
It's simple.
Nothing complicated. The truth is that

132
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:39,760
I just sold shares
that I recently received.

133
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:41,440
So what will you do next?

134
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,680
I've got an idea.

135
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:03,760
<i>All this time, Kluay,</i>

136
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:05,920
<i>I've been using you.</i>

137
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,920
<i>Because I thought</i>
<i>it would make things easier.</i>

138
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:12,040
<i>Let's break up.</i>

139
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:24,440
Yes, Sin?

140
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:27,320
Hello, Kluay. I want to meet you.

141
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:30,240
Lately I've been…

142
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:34,160
I want to meet you. I want to
apologize for what I've done to you,

143
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:35,720
for how I've misunderstood you.

144
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:37,680
It's okay, Sin.

145
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:40,200
I don't hold anything against you.

146
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:41,880
I really need to see you.

147
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,120
Uh…

148
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:48,360
Well, I want to know

149
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:50,760
what really happened that day.
How did Lak die?

150
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:17,240
Hello, Mr. Warat.

151
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:19,000
How is Mrs. Wanee?

152
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:21,680
What can I help you with today?

153
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:23,200
- Inspector.
- Yes?

154
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:25,760
I want to ask
about a case in your area of duty.

155
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,280
This one.

156
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:30,800
This is Mr. Wichan, right?

157
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:32,480
Yes. My father.

158
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:34,120
And?

159
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:39,000
Everyone in this photo is dead,

160
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:40,000
except me.

161
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:43,880
But I believe this woman is still alive.

162
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:46,000
Her name is Waree.

163
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:49,760
She might be the real heir
of my grandmother.

164
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:53,360
I think she disappeared
about 25 years ago.

165
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:55,560
And why do you suddenly

166
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:58,080
want to find her? What's the reason?

167
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:01,880
Because I believe Waree's alive.

168
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:04,480
Ms. Ampha made me see

169
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:07,040
that her daughter is still alive.

170
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:12,119
There's one person
I'm certain would never lie to me.

171
00:17:13,839 --> 00:17:17,359
She told me Waree is still alive.

172
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:21,920
But it won't be easy to find
someone who's been missing for decades.

173
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:28,200
Then, I suggest you start with this case.

174
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:30,000
Pong and Soi.

175
00:17:31,480 --> 00:17:32,640
If I remember correctly,

176
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:35,000
their car caught fire.

177
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:37,320
It was an accident. In the end,

178
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:40,120
both of them were found dead in the car.

179
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:44,600
If you go through the old case files,

180
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:48,760
you might find some clues or information

181
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:49,680
about this woman.

182
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:53,360
- Inspector.
- Yes.

183
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:54,520
I'm counting on you.

184
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:58,240
For me, finding Waree

185
00:17:59,080 --> 00:18:00,640
is very important.

186
00:18:02,360 --> 00:18:03,360
Understood.

187
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:20,800
Let's go home.

188
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,720
This is my house.

189
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:25,400
No, this is my house.

190
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:27,000
I bought it for you.

191
00:18:27,080 --> 00:18:28,640
Come back with me now.

192
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:29,760
No.

193
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:31,840
I'm staying here.

194
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:34,800
You're my daughter.

195
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:36,720
You can stay.

196
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:38,400
But you, get out.

197
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:41,120
- Dad.
- I'm not your dad.

198
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:48,400
But the child in her womb is mine.

199
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:50,280
But I won't accept you.

200
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:51,200
Dad.

201
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:53,000
You don't have the right to call me that.

202
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:55,040
Dad…

203
00:18:56,360 --> 00:18:58,000
Det and I…

204
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,920
love each other.

205
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,600
Nonsense.

206
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:05,640
How can you live with him

207
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:07,640
when he's just a servant's son?

208
00:19:07,720 --> 00:19:10,760
"Servant's son," over and over again.

209
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:13,000
I'll prove it to you

210
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:15,680
that I can take care of Ameena.

211
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,520
But you have no right

212
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:20,800
because I don't allow it.

213
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:23,560
That's fine.

214
00:19:25,280 --> 00:19:27,200
I don't need your permission.

215
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:28,440
Ameena.

216
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:29,360
What?

217
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:32,280
You have a duty
to carry on the family business.

218
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:34,280
The family's business?

219
00:19:35,160 --> 00:19:36,760
Or yours?

220
00:19:36,840 --> 00:19:38,960
Don't you dare talk back to me.

221
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:41,000
What about my child?

222
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:44,360
I'll take care of the child myself.

223
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:48,560
If you choose him, then leave this house.

224
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:51,160
And return everything that belongs to me.

225
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:09,200
Take it all back.

226
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:11,560
I came into this world with nothing,

227
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:13,600
I'll leave with nothing.

228
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:14,920
Ameena.

229
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:17,280
You're just like your mother.

230
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:19,480
Impulsive. Selfish.

231
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:21,560
- You!
- You've never listened to me!

232
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:24,320
You're still young. You don't understand.

233
00:20:24,880 --> 00:20:27,440
Now I know why Mom left you.

234
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:31,440
All this time, I misunderstood her.

235
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:34,640
She was ungrateful.

236
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:36,440
If being grateful to you

237
00:20:36,520 --> 00:20:38,240
means I have to be a bad person,

238
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:40,600
then I choose to be ungrateful.

239
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,640
Stop.

240
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,280
I'm sorry.

241
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:11,840
Thank you…

242
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,960
for raising me all these years.

243
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:38,800
Goodbye, Dad.

244
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:43,360
Huh?

245
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:57,680
Let's go, Det.

246
00:22:18,120 --> 00:22:23,880
Do whatever it takes.
Find Waree before Warat does.

247
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,000
<i>Yes, ma'am.</i>

248
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:28,160
Come in.

249
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:31,560
Sin, what's going on?

250
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:40,560
Sin?

251
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:44,800
That's a lot of money.
Where did you get it?

252
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:46,800
Mom…

253
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:51,240
I don't want to be a tool

254
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:54,280
in the Vanich family's
power struggle anymore.

255
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:56,160
What do you mean?

256
00:22:56,240 --> 00:22:58,320
The kindness
you've shown me all these years,

257
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:01,120
I can never repay it.

258
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:02,720
Sin.

259
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:05,800
That day, I was so happy
when you transferred those shares to me.

260
00:23:07,320 --> 00:23:09,280
But not because of

261
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:11,760
the amount of money. But

262
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:13,880
I was happy because…

263
00:23:13,960 --> 00:23:16,640
you honored me. You gave me a chance

264
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:18,200
to be part of Vanich.

265
00:23:18,280 --> 00:23:20,800
That means more than
the money you gave me.

266
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:23,600
But I was willing to.

267
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:26,840
I was willing to give it to you.

268
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:28,680
Thank you, Mom.

269
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:31,240
This is all the money

270
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:35,760
from selling the shares you gave me.

271
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:40,000
So you sold all of them

272
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:42,520
even though I just gave them to you?

273
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:47,080
Yes. But I didn't sell them for the money.

274
00:23:47,160 --> 00:23:50,600
I wanted to return
every single baht to you.

275
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:53,360
Why would you do that?

276
00:23:54,840 --> 00:23:58,200
Why not help take care of the business?

277
00:23:58,280 --> 00:23:59,800
I want to see you grow.

278
00:24:03,680 --> 00:24:05,800
Who did you sell the shares to?

279
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:08,520
I sold them to Warat.

280
00:24:09,760 --> 00:24:11,240
Warat?

281
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:13,080
I've always respected him

282
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:15,600
as someone I've known,

283
00:24:15,680 --> 00:24:17,320
and I've always respected him

284
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:19,120
as my boss.

285
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,880
Listen to me, Sin.

286
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:24,880
Warat is not your boss.

287
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:29,400
I want to see the two of you
be good partners,

288
00:24:29,480 --> 00:24:31,520
working side-by-side

289
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:33,840
to take care of Vanich together

290
00:24:33,920 --> 00:24:35,880
and make it prosper.

291
00:24:35,960 --> 00:24:39,560
But you know better than anyone,
Warat would never see it that way.

292
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:41,120
He's still young.

293
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:43,440
I know and I understand

294
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:44,920
that sometimes

295
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:49,680
he can be impulsive and stubborn.

296
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:51,320
But you're older.

297
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:54,320
You should understand and let it go.

298
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:56,080
Mom…

299
00:24:57,320 --> 00:24:59,200
Warat hates me.

300
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:01,480
Why would you think that?

301
00:25:02,120 --> 00:25:04,360
He sent Golf to trick me
into selling all my shares.

302
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:05,680
Warat?

303
00:25:08,560 --> 00:25:13,040
And you still agreed to sell everything?

304
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:16,920
Mom, I don't want to be
anyone's tool. I don't…

305
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:21,680
I don't want to be
part of this power struggle.

306
00:25:21,760 --> 00:25:25,000
That's why I returned all the shares
to someone from Vanich.

307
00:25:26,360 --> 00:25:27,880
As for the money,

308
00:25:28,520 --> 00:25:31,440
Mr. Warat and Mr. Golf
don't care about me anyway.

309
00:25:31,520 --> 00:25:34,880
And I don't want anything to do with it.

310
00:25:35,520 --> 00:25:37,160
Sin.

311
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:40,200
The reason I came to tell you first

312
00:25:40,280 --> 00:25:44,360
is because I'm afraid Mr. Warat
will make you misunderstand me.

313
00:25:45,680 --> 00:25:47,120
He'll say

314
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:50,000
I sold the shares because I wanted money.

315
00:25:50,080 --> 00:25:51,560
That I sold them

316
00:25:51,640 --> 00:25:54,080
to take away his power. That I sold them

317
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:57,120
to make Mr. Golf the new executive.

318
00:25:58,120 --> 00:25:59,800
He's already prepared everything to say.

319
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:01,880
Sin,

320
00:26:02,440 --> 00:26:05,720
you don't need to worry about any of that.

321
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:10,600
I understand. I trust you. Don't worry.

322
00:26:11,720 --> 00:26:12,800
Mom.

323
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:15,280
I…

324
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:17,480
I don't want anything

325
00:26:17,560 --> 00:26:22,360
except to repay you for raising me.

326
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:24,880
Sin…

327
00:26:33,560 --> 00:26:35,320
<i>‪Sorry, the number that you've dialed</i>
<i>‪cannot be connected…</i>

328
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:38,840
Darling, Mr. Warat's phone is still off.

329
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:41,160
What did you just call me?

330
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:42,200
Darling.

331
00:26:45,560 --> 00:26:48,800
Arnon, this is moving way too fast.

332
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:49,800
- Uh…
- Mm.

333
00:26:49,880 --> 00:26:52,040
Alright, let's focus
on the important thing first.

334
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:56,640
Right. We still can't reach Mr. Warat.
No idea where he is.

335
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:57,880
Could he be in a meeting?

336
00:26:57,960 --> 00:27:00,680
Unlikely. If it were work-related,

337
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:03,520
I'd know exactly where he is.

338
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:05,480
Where did he go?

339
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:07,920
Wait a second.

340
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:10,400
Right now, there's only one thing

341
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:12,240
Mr. Warat is focused on.

342
00:27:12,840 --> 00:27:14,720
Finding Waree, right?

343
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:18,880
Then why didn't he ask you to help?

344
00:27:18,960 --> 00:27:21,040
Maybe he has his reasons.

345
00:27:21,120 --> 00:27:24,040
What reasons?
And where would he even look?

346
00:27:24,120 --> 00:27:26,160
Why didn't he take you with him?

347
00:27:28,560 --> 00:27:31,280
Let's think about it.

348
00:27:31,360 --> 00:27:36,600
Where would he go to find information?

349
00:27:38,080 --> 00:27:40,640
Ugh, I have no idea.

350
00:27:40,720 --> 00:27:42,720
We've already checked everything,
haven't we?

351
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:45,920
Even about Pong and Soi.

352
00:27:47,160 --> 00:27:52,320
Or maybe he went to the office
to look into their information?

353
00:27:52,400 --> 00:27:54,040
Then should we go check the office?

354
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:05,680
Ms. Ampha.

355
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:09,360
Where are you right now?

356
00:28:17,640 --> 00:28:18,800
Ms. Ampha.

357
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:23,360
Now Mr. Warat's missing too.

358
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:28,600
Where are you?

359
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:33,320
What did I see earlier?

360
00:28:47,080 --> 00:28:48,400
Ms. Ampha.

361
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:17,440
Ms. Ampha.

362
00:29:18,040 --> 00:29:19,040
Ms. Ampha.

363
00:29:19,120 --> 00:29:20,320
Ms. Ampha.

364
00:29:20,400 --> 00:29:21,840
Ms. Ampha, what happened?

365
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:23,720
Ms. Ampha.

366
00:29:30,440 --> 00:29:31,520
Ms. Ampha.

367
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:34,560
What's going on with you?

368
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:51,360
Mr. Warat, Ms. Ampha's in trouble.
Where did you go?

369
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:06,600
I've taken care of everything.

370
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:09,840
- But the evidence…
- I already gave her all the money.

371
00:30:09,920 --> 00:30:11,040
She'll believe it.

372
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:13,520
Then what's left for us?

373
00:30:14,600 --> 00:30:17,200
Your position.
And my position as her favorite.

374
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:20,480
No, I mean the money.

375
00:30:21,120 --> 00:30:22,800
Think of it as a deposit.

376
00:30:23,520 --> 00:30:26,040
When we get it back,
I'll take it back with interest.

377
00:30:30,960 --> 00:30:32,360
Mr. Warat still hasn't shown up?

378
00:30:32,440 --> 00:30:33,880
Not yet.

379
00:30:33,960 --> 00:30:35,320
What about Ms. Kluay?

380
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:37,280
I haven't seen her either.

381
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:40,840
If you see either of them,
can you call me right away?

382
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,480
I need to talk to them urgently.

383
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:45,360
Of course. I'll call you immediately.

384
00:30:45,440 --> 00:30:46,800
Thank you.

385
00:30:51,480 --> 00:30:54,640
Or could Mr. Warat
and Ms. Kluay have gone together?

386
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:57,000
Where would they go?

387
00:30:57,080 --> 00:31:00,080
They just broke up. I don't think so.

388
00:31:00,160 --> 00:31:01,680
Well, Som,

389
00:31:02,280 --> 00:31:03,920
maybe it's like

390
00:31:04,480 --> 00:31:06,720
they went to clear things up.

391
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:09,160
I don't think so.

392
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:10,320
At the Vanich house,

393
00:31:10,400 --> 00:31:13,360
Kluay said Mr. Warat told her
not to leave the house at all.

394
00:31:13,440 --> 00:31:15,920
What? He went that far?

395
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:18,960
That doesn't sound like
people who have broken up.

396
00:31:20,080 --> 00:31:24,360
I think Mr. Warat
might be doing something dangerous.

397
00:31:26,720 --> 00:31:30,280
I've got something. From the records,

398
00:31:30,360 --> 00:31:32,520
this was ruled an accident.

399
00:31:32,600 --> 00:31:34,240
Two fatalities,

400
00:31:34,840 --> 00:31:36,240
Pong and Soi.

401
00:31:36,320 --> 00:31:38,160
But there's something strange.

402
00:31:42,480 --> 00:31:43,600
Baan Saeng Wan Mai?

403
00:31:43,680 --> 00:31:46,680
Yes. If you contact them,

404
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:49,400
you might get more clues about that girl.

405
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:52,360
If she's still alive,

406
00:31:53,720 --> 00:31:55,400
she'd be around…

407
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:58,480
About 25 years old.

408
00:31:59,880 --> 00:32:01,280
Thank you, Inspector.

409
00:32:18,400 --> 00:32:20,880
Lak, how are you? Are you okay?

410
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:28,880
I miss you every day.

411
00:32:34,760 --> 00:32:36,240
Why did you leave me alone?

412
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:45,000
Ever since everyone left,

413
00:32:48,680 --> 00:32:50,560
I've never been happy again.

414
00:32:56,160 --> 00:32:58,280
There's so much I want to tell you, Lak.

415
00:33:02,880 --> 00:33:04,440
Once I finish everything,

416
00:33:06,760 --> 00:33:08,080
I'll go be with you, Lak.

417
00:33:17,280 --> 00:33:18,280
It's getting late.

418
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,960
Babe, do you think
Mr. Warat will come to the office?

419
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:22,640
What?

420
00:33:22,720 --> 00:33:24,240
Will Mr. Warat come to the office?

421
00:33:24,320 --> 00:33:26,920
I mean, the word before that.

422
00:33:27,520 --> 00:33:28,560
Babe?

423
00:33:30,040 --> 00:33:31,360
- Arnon…
- What?

424
00:33:31,440 --> 00:33:33,240
Why don't you just
call me Som like before?

425
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:36,120
Well, our relationship has changed.

426
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:38,320
Ugh. No.

427
00:33:38,400 --> 00:33:40,320
I'm not used to it. It's too soon.

428
00:33:40,920 --> 00:33:44,480
Alright then,
I'll call you that once a day,

429
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:46,080
so,

430
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:48,760
you can get used to it, darling.

431
00:33:50,400 --> 00:33:51,760
Darling?

432
00:33:52,880 --> 00:33:54,960
- I'm going now.
- Okay.

433
00:33:55,040 --> 00:33:56,680
Your necklace looks beautiful.

434
00:34:04,160 --> 00:34:05,280
Come in.

435
00:34:06,360 --> 00:34:09,159
Oh, Arnon. Are you here for work?

436
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:12,199
Yes, I'm here for work.

437
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:16,000
Mrs. Wanee, have you seen Mr. Warat?

438
00:34:16,719 --> 00:34:20,199
No, I didn't see him
before I left this morning.

439
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:23,679
Have you checked his office?
Maybe he's there.

440
00:34:23,760 --> 00:34:25,080
He's not there.

441
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:29,120
Uh…

442
00:34:29,199 --> 00:34:30,480
Those documents…

443
00:34:30,560 --> 00:34:33,639
I'm glad you're here, Arnon.

444
00:34:34,239 --> 00:34:35,719
So,

445
00:34:35,800 --> 00:34:39,320
what exactly is going on
between Warat and Jirasin?

446
00:34:41,280 --> 00:34:45,120
Actually, I wanted Mr. Warat
to explain it to you himself,

447
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:49,000
but let me explain instead.

448
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:50,639
To be fair,

449
00:34:50,719 --> 00:34:53,120
should we call
Mr. Jirasin and Mr. Chatchai

450
00:34:53,199 --> 00:34:54,679
to hear it together?

451
00:34:54,760 --> 00:34:56,639
Let's settle everything at once.

452
00:35:10,560 --> 00:35:12,000
Where should we go?

453
00:35:13,320 --> 00:35:15,080
Where should we run to?

454
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:17,800
We could just stay at the condo.

455
00:35:19,120 --> 00:35:20,240
We'd better not.

456
00:35:22,480 --> 00:35:24,240
I know my father.

457
00:35:25,560 --> 00:35:28,080
He's probably
waiting for us there already.

458
00:35:30,720 --> 00:35:32,120
Then what do we do?

459
00:35:33,960 --> 00:35:35,320
I'm ready.

460
00:35:36,520 --> 00:35:38,360
Are you ready, Det?

461
00:35:51,640 --> 00:35:53,560
No, we're not going to die.

462
00:35:55,040 --> 00:35:56,600
Who said anything about dying?

463
00:35:56,680 --> 00:35:58,600
Oh? Then…

464
00:35:59,640 --> 00:36:00,760
what do you mean by "ready"?

465
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:03,040
I mean

466
00:36:04,160 --> 00:36:05,960
I'm ready to run away with you.

467
00:36:06,040 --> 00:36:07,520
Have you really thought this through?

468
00:36:19,680 --> 00:36:23,040
Ten years ago, when we were young,

469
00:36:23,600 --> 00:36:27,000
we didn't understand the difference

470
00:36:27,080 --> 00:36:28,560
between someone like you

471
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:30,480
and someone like me.

472
00:36:32,280 --> 00:36:34,120
- Don't tell me you…
- But,

473
00:36:34,200 --> 00:36:35,720
now that we've grown up,

474
00:36:36,440 --> 00:36:37,880
it made me understand

475
00:36:39,880 --> 00:36:41,560
that you running away with me

476
00:36:42,440 --> 00:36:43,520
is impossible.

477
00:36:48,120 --> 00:36:49,440
Listen to me.

478
00:36:51,160 --> 00:36:53,520
Nothing is impossible.

479
00:37:01,840 --> 00:37:03,440
But do you realize
what you have to give up?

480
00:37:05,680 --> 00:37:06,960
It doesn't matter

481
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:09,600
what I have to give up.

482
00:37:13,800 --> 00:37:14,920
Right now,

483
00:37:16,040 --> 00:37:17,600
what matters the most

484
00:37:19,400 --> 00:37:20,720
is you

485
00:37:21,760 --> 00:37:24,160
and our child.

486
00:37:32,080 --> 00:37:33,800
What are you looking at? Drive.

487
00:37:34,880 --> 00:37:36,280
- Okay.
- Hurry.

488
00:37:46,200 --> 00:37:49,400
<i>You see? Arnon was hired</i>
<i>by a competitor to destroy us.</i>

489
00:37:50,160 --> 00:37:52,080
<i>No wonder Mr. Jirasin kept telling me</i>

490
00:37:52,160 --> 00:37:54,360
someone was targeting Mr. Warat.

491
00:37:54,440 --> 00:37:55,760
NEXT EPISODE

492
00:37:55,840 --> 00:37:57,240
<i>Every time something went wrong,</i>

493
00:37:57,320 --> 00:38:01,160
<i>weren't you the one who protected Kluay?</i>

494
00:38:01,240 --> 00:38:06,480
If you two love each other, you should
hold on to each other even tighter.

495
00:38:07,080 --> 00:38:09,560
Jirasin, if you don't stop,

496
00:38:09,640 --> 00:38:10,880
I'll crash into you.

497
00:38:14,360 --> 00:38:15,720
<i>I'm going to take everything back.</i>

498
00:38:17,040 --> 00:38:18,400
<i>Everything that should be mine.</i>

499
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:50,720
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
